                          --AMIGADOS GUIDE V2.6--
                                   FAULT


   USE:
   Fault is used to give an explanation of a selected AmigaDOS error.

   PATH:
   Internal

   SYSTEM:
   2.0, 2.1, 3.0

   EXAMPLES:
   1>FAULT 218
   Fault 218: device (or volume) not mounted.

   NOTES:
   Fault can also return explanations of up to 10 error codes, separated
   by either commas or spaces. (see below)

   1>FAULT 105 106 214
   FAULT 105: task table full
   FAULT 106: error 106
   FAULT 214: disk write protected
